TITLE: Serializing Objects to JSON in C#
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to serialize a C# object to JSON string using JsonConvert.SerializeObject(). The example shows serialization of a Product object with various property types including string, DateTime, and array.
SOURCE: https://github.com/JamesNK/Newtonsoft.Json/blob/master/Src/Newtonsoft.Json/README.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
Product product = new Product();
product.Name = "Apple";
product.Expiry = new DateTime(2008, 12, 28);
product.Sizes = new string[] { "Small" };

string json = JsonConvert.SerializeObject(product);
// {
//   "Name": "Apple",
//   "Expiry": "2008-12-28T00:00:00",
//   "Sizes": [
//     "Small"
//   ]
// }
```

