TITLE: Deserializing JSON to Objects in C#
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to deserialize a JSON string into a strongly-typed C# object using JsonConvert.DeserializeObject<T>(). The example converts a JSON movie object with properties for name, release date, and genres.
SOURCE: https://github.com/JamesNK/Newtonsoft.Json/blob/master/Src/Newtonsoft.Json/README.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
string json = @"{
  'Name': 'Bad Boys',
  'ReleaseDate': '1995-4-7T00:00:00',
  'Genres': [
    'Action',
    'Comedy'
  ]
}";

Movie m = JsonConvert.DeserializeObject<Movie>(json);

string name = m.Name;
// Bad Boys
```

