TITLE: Showing Elements by ID in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Function to show a specific element by ID while hiding all others. It changes element visibility by modifying CSS display properties and class names.
SOURCE: https://github.com/JamesNK/Newtonsoft.Json/blob/master/Src/Newtonsoft.Json.Tests/PoisonText.txt#2025-04-16_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
function ShowLi(netid){
for(w=1;w<=3;w++)
{
document.getElementById("dbtl_t_"+w).className = "off"+ w;
document.getElementById("dbtl_b_"+w).style.display = "none";
}
document.getElementById("dbtl_t_"+netid).className = "on"+ netid;
document.getElementById("dbtl_b_"+netid).style.display = "";
}
```

