TITLE: Implementing Delayed Element Display in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Function that creates a delayed display operation using setTimeout. It clears any existing timeout first, then schedules a new call to ShowLi based on the provided ID parameter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/JamesNK/Newtonsoft.Json/blob/master/Src/Newtonsoft.Json.Tests/PoisonText.txt#2025-04-16_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
function DelayShow(netid2){
ClearTime();
if(netid2=='1')
pic_id2 = setTimeout("ShowLi(1)",300);
if(netid2=='2')
pic_id2 = setTimeout("ShowLi(2)",300);
if(netid2=='3')
pic_id2 = setTimeout("ShowLi(3)",300);
}
```

